article.headline: North Texas 82, Arkansas State 79
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- Kendrick Davis and Isaac Hines scored scored 17 points each to help North Texas get an 82-79 come-from-behind victory Saturday over Arkansas State. North Texas (11-6, 4-2 Sun Belt Conference) trailed 37-31 at intermission, but surged back to outscore the Indians (8-13, 3-4) 51-42 in the second half. Hines' scoring included 3-of-4 from 3-point range. He and Davis also set the pace for the Mean Green at the free-throw line, with Hines hitting 2-of-2 and Davis going 6-for-6 as their team hit 21-of-24 foul shots. The Indians fell far short of that mark, despite many more opportunities, making just 23-of-37 free throws. Harold Edwards added 11 points for North Texas, while Calvin Watson and Jeffrey Simpson came off the bench to score 10 each. Isaac Wells led ASU with 20 points, with Marcus Ardison adding 14, Dereke Tipler 12, Yual Hanks 11 and Jim Jones 10.
